Abstract = {Intraspecific varaition has been found several pollination-related
   characteristics in two isolated populations of the self-incompatible
   tree Acacia terminalis; floral characteristics including colour and
   flowering time: style length, size and colour of extrafloral nectaries
   on the leaf petioles; chemical components of the extrafloral nectar;
   different taxa of bee pollinators; and frequency differences in bird
   pollinators. These differences possibly reflect the evolution of two
   different  pollination syndromes within this species.},
